Zoo Performance car cleaning  range including everything you need to give your car the TLC it deserves.  Our products are safe to use on all paint surfaces and finishes, including ceramic coating, chrome, alloy, glass and non-porous plastics.  We know cars and we know parts, so we thought it was time to produce the perfect aftercare products to allow a flawless car wash and quality finish anywhere, anytime!

The Essentials Kit Includes;
1 x Black Waterproof Carry Bag
1 x Microfibre Charcoal Cloth with hanging loop (50cm x 60cm)
1 x 500ML Extreme Snow Foam Car Wash - Bubblegum Scented!
1 x 500ML Waterless Wash & Wax Solution Spray - Vanilla Scented!
1 x 500ML Iron Wheel & Tyre Cleaner Spray - Grape Scented!
1 x 500ML Ceramic Coating Protection Spray - Coconut Scented!
1 X 500ML Bug and Tar Remover Spray - Peach Scented!



About the Products in this Kit

"Talk Dirty to Me" Extreme Snow Foam Car Wash
Our extreme wash snow foam offers exceptional cleaning capabilities through advanced
foaming technology to effectively remove dirt, dust and oil stains from the vehicle surface.  It’s bubblegum scented formula contains specialised cleaning agents that can penetrate and break down even the toughest of grime for a enhanced clean and brilliant shine.

Our innovative snow foam is designed with the perfect pH balance to remove tough dirt and debris while safely maintaining your vehicle’s wax or sealant. Our snowfoam works great with any foam gun or foam cannon for the perfect
touch-free wash.

"Dirty Little Secret" Waterless Wash & Wax Solution
Our vanilla scented waterless wash and wax is the 1-step solution to a enhanced detailed look for your
vehicle. Clean, protect and shine with our waterless system and provide durable
long-lasting protection with the optimal gloss-shine finish.

Our specially designed pH balanced formula is perfect for all paint surfaces, chrome and
alloy wheels, glass, bumpers, plastics and more. Look no further than our Waterless Wash and Wax, designed for car enthusiasts to allow the perfect car wash and quality finish anywhere, anytime.

"Purple Gold" Iron Wheel & Tyre Cleaner
Iron contaminates, brake dust and grime are no match against our powerful
Iron Remover Wheel Cleaner. This revolutionary grape scented formula breaks down even the toughest, stubborn dirt from the surface of any vehicle while carefully preserving paintwork and wheels.

Our wheel cleaner easily removes road grime and heavy brake dust to restore
your wheels and will leave your vehicle with an exceptional clean surface finish.
Effortlessly easy to use and safe to use on paint, chrome, alloy, glass, wheels and
most plastics.

"Ceramic Armour" Coating Protection Spray
Our ceramic protection spray is formulated using a flurosilicone polymer to form a
crystal-like film over the paint surface for the maximum amount of protection. The film
creates a barrier to repel water, shed contaminants and enables self-cleaning.
It can be safely used on both coated and non-coated vehicles.

Our coconut-scented ceramic spray forms a unpenetrable protection armour not only against water and dirt but prevents discolouration from UV Rays, water spots and other harsh environment conditions. Whether you looking for paint protection, the ultimate shine-finish or to extend the condition of your vehicle’s surface inbetween washes, our ceramic armour will keep

"Rubber Be Gone" Bug and Tar Remover

Tackle the toughest stains and grime with our Bug & Tar Remover. This easy to use
concentrated formula penetrates and dissolves stubborn road tar, stains, insects,
grime and bird droppings for a spot-free clean surface finish.

No hard scubbing required and leaves behind an immaculate clean surface.
Our Bug and Tar remover is safe to use on all paint surfaces, chrome, alloy glass and
non-porous plastic. Perfect for removing stubburn baked-on stickers and livery residue.

Invisible Protecive Barrier shield against UV rays and harsh Australian conditons.

Our ceramic protection spray is formulated using a flurosilicone polymer to form a

Directions:
Pre-wash the vehicle surface with our extreme wash snow foam. Leave to Dry.
Shake bottle thoroughly and use only in a shaded area away from direct sunlight.
Hold the bottle 20-30cm away from the vehicle and spray ceramic protection evenly
onto paint surface in small sections. Use a slighly damp microfibre cloth or towel
to wipe clean.

Dimethicone (CAS 63148-62-9) Methylphenyl silicone resin (CAS 67763-03-5)
Polyethylene Glycol Alkylphenyl Ether (CAS 9041-29-6) Deionized Water (CAS 7732-18-5) Artifical colouring and fragrance.

WARNING
Keep out of reach of children and pets.
If accidentially swallowed - Immediatley call a doctor or Poison Hotline.
Eyes: For eye contact, rinse thoroughly with water for 15 minutes.
In Case of Contact with Skin; Wash thoroughly with soap and water.
If irritation persists, contact a doctor. Use only in well ventilated areas.

column3:
ZOO PERFORMANCE Turbo Beanies or Turbo Blankets, are constructed using a high temperature pure carbon fibre & titanium material combined with a silica insulation matting under a tight weaved outer layer and a stainless steel reinforced cage. This premium technology is heat rated to 1270 °C both internally and externally. Our new double wall design is created to reduce as much heat as possible from your engine bay and surrounding components.

Turbo beanies are used to separate the turbine housing from the core.  This allows the core to work with less heat strain,  resulting in less of a chance of failing.  The heat energy stays stored within the gas, hotter gases accelerate far better than cooler gases, so reducing the overall effect that it would have on the turbo's lifespan. 

Each Turbo Beanie comes with stainless steel anchoring hooks incorporated into the sheild, as well as spring clips for securing.  

AVAILABLE SIZES: 
T28, T3, T4, T6

COLOURS: 
Carbon Fibre, Titanium

column2: G50-1900 HP Series 88mm Turbo - Stainless Steel Rear Housing
column3:
G50-1900 HP Series 88mm Turbo - Stainless Steel Housing

- 1000-1900HP Rating   / 2.5L - 11.0L Displacement
- Dual Ball Bearing
- Ported shroud compressor cover
- Speed sensor port included in compressor cover.
- Inlet Options:   

  • 1.31 A/R with V-Band Inlet

- Compressor Specifications:

  • 88mm Compressor Inducer wheel
  • 120mm Compressor Exducer wheel
  • 0.88 A/R
  • Inlet Size:  6" Hose 
  • Outlet Size: 4.21" Hose

- Turbine Specifications:

  • 99mm Turbine Inducer wheel
  • 94mm Turbine Exducer wheel
  • Inlet Size:  3.8" Hose
  • Outlet Size: 4.5" Hose
  • Stainless Steel Turbine Housing

- Fittings: 

  • Water Ports: N/A 
  • Oil Inlet: 7/16-24 UNF with a -4AN Restrictor pre-installed.
  • Oil Outlet: 50.8mm (Centre to Centre) Oil Drain Flange
  • Oil Outlet Flange Bolt Size 2 x M8 x 1.25

Our G50 series turbos are manufactured specifically with a combination of the highest quality components and exquisite design with no expense spared! The dual ceramic ball bearing design provides an optimal turbo response and prolongs the lifespan of your turbo.

Our G50 series turbos are fitted with a 13-blade point milled billet aluminium compressor wheel with an aerodynamic tapered tip. The aluminium compressor housing is also fitted with a sensor port. Our compressor wheels are designed with the latest technology maximizing horsepower and boost response and have temperature ratings of up to 200°C. The compressor housings are also fitted with a speed sensor port as well as an anti-surge compressor wheel inlet to increase surge resistance and provides reliable, continuous power.

The turbine wheel is manufactured from Inconel which is a high quality super alloy and does a fantastic job at maintaining strength at high operating temperatures of up to 900°C. Our turbine housings are made from a high grade stainless steel providing ultimate durability in these high performance applications.  

Each and every turbo are supplied with all the required parts such as stainless steel polished v-band clamps, flanges, water fittings, turbo drain gasket and NPT 1/4" to -4AN turbo oil feed fitting with 1.6mm restrictor hole. We strongly recommend running an oil pressure regulator with all of our turbos.

This 108mm cable LS billet throttle body is the first of its kind to be released to the Australian market. Key features of this unit include, optimum sealing under boost and low air speed stability ensuring idle control and transient throttle inputs.  

They have been developed using one of our in house tuners, to ensure tuning is a breeze.  Adding to our already extensive range,  our engineers have produced this throttle body for those who were restricted by the previous current models on the market,  and they are designed to eliminate any and all size limitations without compromising on quality or looks. 

Our throttle body can be used in conjunction with fast intakes, standard intakes or aftermarket intakes (minimal modifications may be required) 

These are available in either a hard anodised black or polished silver options to suit your style and look.

  • 108mm diameter opening
  • 2.5mm thick copper butterfly plate 
  • Thick 24mm flange
  • 4 bolt mounting (hardware included)
  • Corrosion resistant split shaft
  • Sealed ball bearings to provide smooth butterfly motion.


**We are pleased to offer a 2 year direct replaceemnt warranty in the unlikely event of a fault or issue.

We are proud to release our early model Holden Commodore LS Manifold and custom LS Turbo Kit.

We’ve partnered up with some awesome local people and businesses who have been in the industry for many years to develop these kits and they are engineered and manufactured right here in Australia. 

It’s a 4 into 1 merge collector, NB40 steam pipe runner, NB65 merge to T4, T6 or V-Band flange including a wastegate provision (when a Zoo Performance wastegate is purchased) and finished with a 3” stainless steel crossover with a flex join.
We're providing this as either a manifold only or optioned up kit including your choice of turbo, wastegate, intercooler, BOV and heat proof products.

You can custom order your kit to opt for wastegate merge for in guard placement for a tidier bay, EGT ports and your choice of our high temp ceramic coating colours. 

If you are fitting a non-Zoo Performance wastegate, please advise brand,sizing & flange so we can include provisions.

Suits Models:
HOLDEN COMMODORE
VB, VC, VH, VK, VL, VN, VP, VR, VS

Manifolds Only:
-  Manifold with your choice of inlet and colours including High Temp Black or Thermal Ceramic Coated. 

LS Turbo Kit: 
Automatically receive 15% off our performance parts when purchased as a package.  

- Manifold  (High Temp Black or Thermal Ceramic Coated)
- NB40 Steam Pipe Runners
- NB65 Merge to T6 Flange or V-Band
- 3" Stainless Steel Crossover with Flex Join
- Turbo & Turbo Beanie
- Intercooler 
- Wastegate & Wastegate Beanie
- BOV
- Other heat management items 

(If you require your turbo without oil feed please contact us directly)

column3:
2 Litre aluminium catch can with drain tap

Designed for amazing appearance,  simple mounting and high performance applications.
Our catch cans are precision robot welded using high quality 5052 aluminium. 

Using a tapered -AN10 banjo style plug to achieve a spill free solution while draining and each catch can is supplied with a Zoo Performance baffled breather filter to prevent carbon build up and is essential in removing PCV oil before it travels through your precious engine.

- 2LT: 280mm overall height,  160mm wide,  125mm deep
- BREATHER/FILTER: AN12 Female Port, 90mm height, 75mm wide

column2: Custom Performance Axles -  Made to your specs!
column3:
Zoo Performance have been manufacturing our own custom axles for over 2 years and they have been produced with extreme durability to suit all types of performance cars including speedway, drag cars, road or rally racing. 
We offer the highest quality axles made from the perfect combination of heat treated shafts made from from 40CrNi2Si2MoVA steel and flanges from high quality structural carbon 55 grade steel and they are made to be pushed to their limits in any motorsport.

We have a few options available starting with custom axles rated to 1200HP and also a monster 2000HP set,  all of our axles are custom made with precision accurancy from your supplied measurements.

If you are looking to upgrade your axles or replace your current set, please contact the team today. We are more than happy to guide you through the process from start to finish.

Please note**
Approx 5-7mm of lateral play is required per axle,  adjustment of suspension may be required to allow the recommended play.

column2: Universal Billet Oil Cooler Sandwich Plate
column3:
Our NEW universal billet oil cooler sandwich plate is designed to sit in-between your oil filter and engine block and also allows an adaptation of a gauge sender or sensors to be installed at the engine.

They are manufactured with the highest quality billet 6061 aluminium and hard anodised black to avoid corrosion.  Designed with 2 x -AN10 ORB inlet/outlet ports for running the engine oil to and from the sandwich adapter,  also included in the design are 2 x 1/8" NPT ports to run a gauge or sensor and an extra thick o-ring for optimum sealing.

This kit includes the below thread inserts that suit most makes and models, 
In most cases your factory oil filter will work with this sandwich adaptor.  however it is a universal fitment item and modifications or adaptors may be required. 

  • 2 x -10AN ORB Adaptors
  • 3/4"-16 thread insert
  • M20*1.5mm thread insert

Seal:

  • I.D: 65mm  (2-7/16')
  • O.D: 71mm  (3-3/8')

column3:
Our GTX5533R Series turbos are manufactured specifically with a combination of the highest quality components and exquisite design with no expense spared!

The triple ceramic ball bearing design provides an optimal turbo response and prolongs the lifespan of your turbo. Our GTX55 series turbos are fitted with an 13-blade point milled billet aluminium compressor wheel with an aerodynamic tapered tip secured inside an aluminium compressor housing, and fitted with a sensor port. Our compressor wheels are designed with the latest engineering that maximizes horsepower and boost response and are also temperature rated up to 200°C. Each turbo is fitted with an anti-surge ported-shroud compressor inlet to increase surge resistance and provides reliable, continuous power.

The turbine wheel is manufactured from Inconel which is a high quality super alloy and does a fantastic job at maintaining strength at high operating temperatures of up to 900°C.  Our turbine housings are made from a high grade cast iron providing ultimate durability in these high performance applications.

Turbine housing are available with a V-Band or T6 Inlet. Each and every turbo are supplied with all the required parts such as stainless steel polished v-band clamps, flanges, water fittings, turbo drain gasket and NPT 1/4" to -4AN turbo oil feed fitting with 1.6mm restrictor hole. We strongly recommend running an oil pressure regulator with all of our turbos.

GTX5533R Specifications:

- 1000-2500HP Rating  / 3.0L - 12.0L Displacement
- Triple Ball Bearing
- Ported shroud compressor cover
- Speed sensor port included in compressor cover.
- Inlet Options:   

  • 1.24 A/R with V-Band Inlet
  • 1.41 A/R with V-Band Inlet
  • 1.24 A/R with T6 Inlet 

- Compressor Specifications:

  • 94mm Compressor Inducer wheel
  • 133mm Compressor Exducer wheel
  • 0.96 A/R

- Turbine Specifications:

  • 112mm Turbine Inducer wheel
  • 102mm Turbine Exducer wheel

Our 200 Series (PTFE) stainless steel fittings are great for applications such as running turbo feed lines, brake, clutch, power steering, hydraulic systems, nitrous or any petrol or alcohol based fuels. These fittings incorporate swivel heads for easy angle adjustment.

Compatible with our 200 Series PTFE nylon and stainless steel hose.

Our Zoo Performance straightening tool is a must have when working with coiled aluminium, mild steel and stainless steel tubing.
It is manufactured from high quality billet aluminium with heavy duty hardwear & mechanisms. 

How to use:
Secure the tool in your workship vice and feed your tube/pipe through the seamless nylon rollers to ensure no scratches or damages for a professional finish.

This tool will work best with 3/16", 5/16", 3/8" & 1/2" tubes

Our tube cutter is suitable to use on plastic, aluminium or steel tubing from 1/8" up to 1-1/8"  (4mm-28mm).

It is extremely durable and designed with an easy-to-use tightening mechanism for a clean sharp cut and also fitted with wide rollers for even tracking of cutter wheel.

Our fire extinguisher mount is manufactured from CNC machined 6061-T6 billet aluminum fitted with an anodised quick-release pull knob to ensure to quickest possible access in an emergency. Mount can be installed in just about any location and designed to accommodate various fire extinguishers. 

Clamps are sold separately.
Features:

  • Machined from billet aluminum
  • Black anodised finish
  • Quick release lever
  • Aprox 12.5cm long x 5cm high x 5cm deep

Our triple pump surge tank makes it simple and easy to upgrade your OEM fuel delivery system without having to make heavy modifications.

It can mount up to 3 EFI fuel pumps or any 40mm diameter fuel pumps and is hard anodised for longevity, durability and corrosion against E85 and methanol.

Specifications include:

  • 140mm diameter faceplate and sits 220mm tall
  • Requires a 4" diameter cutout with 8 x mounting bolts (provided) and to be used with 250mm or 10" deep tanks
  • -10 ORB outlet for maximum flow

Our G25 Series turbos are manufactured specifically with a combination of the highest quality components and exquisite design with no expense spared!

The dual ceramic ball bearing design provides an optimal turbo response and prolongs the lifespan of your turbo. Our G25 series turbos are fitted with a 9-blade aluminium compressor wheel with an aerodynamic tapered tip secured inside an aluminium compressor housing.

Our compressor wheels are designed with the latest technology maximizing horsepower and boost response and have temperature ratings of up to 200°C. The compressor housings are also fitted with a speed sensor port as well as an anti-surge compressor wheel inlet to increase surge resistance and provides reliable, continuous power.

The turbine wheel is manufactured from Inconel which is a high quality super alloy and does a fantastic job at maintaining strength at high operating temperatures of up to 900°C.  Our turbine housings are made from a high grade cast iron providing ultimate durability in these high performance applications.

Turbine housing options include V-band inlet and T3 inlet single scroll. Each and every turbo are supplied with all the required parts such as stainless steel polished v-band clamps, flanges, water fittings, turbo drain gasket and NPT 1/4" to -4AN turbo oil feed fitting with 0.9mm restrictor hole.  We strongly recommend running an oil pressure regulator with all of our turbos.

- Dual Ball Bearing

This is a one-of-a-kind Australian engineered and designed RB head oil drain kit, and is suitable for all RB25/26 heads including NEO. 

This kit has been specifically designed to help reduce a common problem of excessive oil build up in the cylinder heads. With a minimum of two securing points for additional holding strength and strain relief (using OEM fastener locations) so you DO NOT have to drill and tap, this is a direct bolt on solution. 

Manufactured from aircraft grade billet 6061 T6 aluminium and hard anodised black for a sleek glossy look. 

Our RB kit has an extremely low profile at only 45mm thick and fitted with a keyed rotational adjustment for additional strength in motorsport environments and to help route your line safely and securely. 

Suits AN10 ORB fittings.

column2: Mirror Set GEN II GTX3582R Series 66mm Turbo
column3:
Our GEN II GTX3582R Mirror set turbos are manufactured specifically with a combination of the highest quality components and exquisite design with no expense spared!

The dual ceramic ball bearing design provides an optimal turbo response and prolongs the lifespan of your turbo. Our GTX35 Mirror set turbos are fitted with a 10-blade point milled billet aluminium compressor wheel with an aerodynamic tapered tip secured inside an aluminium compressor housing, and fitted with a sensor port. Our compressor wheels are designed with the latest engineering that maximizes horsepower and boost response and are also temperature rated up to 200°C. Each turbo is fitted with an anti-surge ported-shroud compressor inlet to increase surge resistance and provides reliable, continuous power.

The turbine wheel is manufactured from Inconel which is a high quality super alloy and does a fantastic job at maintaining strength at high operating temperatures of up to 900°C.  Our turbine housings are made from a high grade cast iron providing ultimate durability in these high performance applications.

Turbine housing options include V-band inlet, T3 & T4 inlet single scroll. Each and every turbo are supplied with all the required parts such as stainless steel polished v-band clamps, flanges, water fittings, turbo drain gasket and NPT 1/4" to -4AN turbo oil feed fitting with 0.9mm restrictor hole.  We strongly recommend running an oil pressure regulator with all of our turbos.

GEN II GTX3582R Specifications:

- 450-900HP Rating   / 2.0L - 4.5L Displacement
- Dual Ball Bearing
- Ported shroud compressor cover
- Speed sensor port included in compressor cover.
- Inlet Options:   

  • 0.83 A/R with V-Band Inlet
  • 1.01 A/R with V-Band Inlet
  • 0.63 A/R with T3 Inlet
  • 0.82 A/R with T3 Inlet
  • 1.06 A/R with T3 Inlet

- Compressor Specifications:

  • 66mm Compressor Inducer wheel
  • 82mm Compressor Exducer wheel
  • 0.70 A/R

- Turbine Specifications:

  • 68mm Turbine Inducer wheel
  • 62mm Turbine Exducer wheel

We strongly recommend running an oil pressure regulator with all of our turbos.

Our G30 Series turbos are manufactured specifically with a combination of the highest quality components and exquisite design with no expense spared!

The dual ceramic ball bearing design provides an optimal turbo response and prolongs the lifespan of your turbo. Our G30 series turbos are fitted with a 9-blade point milled billet aluminium compressor wheel with an aerodynamic tapered tip secured inside an aluminium compressor housing.

Our compressor wheels are designed with the latest technology maximizing horsepower and boost response and have temperature ratings of up to 200°C. The compressor housings are also fitted with a speed sensor port as well as an anti-surge compressor wheel inlet to increase surge resistance and provides reliable, continuous power.

The turbine wheel is manufactured from Inconel which is a high quality super alloy and does a fantastic job at maintaining strength at high operating temperatures of up to 900°C.  Our turbine housings are made from a high grade cast iron providing ultimate durability in these high performance applications.

Turbine housing options include V-band inlet and T3 inlet single scroll. Each and every turbo are supplied with all the required parts such as stainless steel polished v-band clamps, flanges, water fittings, turbo drain gasket and NPT 1/4" to -4AN turbo oil feed fitting with 0.9mm restrictor hole.  We strongly recommend running an oil pressure regulator with all of our turbos.

RB SERIES - OEM 

These spline driven oil pump gears are manufactured from Billet 4340 steel and are made to suit RB25 Neo and later mode RB26 oil pumps.

These gears are designed with a special wave profile to ensure higher flow rate. 

They are heat-treated to make sure they'll last under the toughest performance conditions. These gears are drastically stronger than the standard gears which are prone to failure on modified vehicles.

Our gears have undergone harsh testing and are QC checked by our own team here in Australia,  tolerances are all within 0.02 thou and therefore we can guarantee the same tolerances in all the gears, no variants at all.

Our adhesive heat shield sheets are supplied in a 500mm x 500mm sheet and can be cut as required to any custom size.

These heat sheets are used as a thermal barrier and can deflect up to 80% of all radiant heat resulting in a dramatic reduction of heat transfer. 
Main uses and applications are intake pipes, exhausts, fire walls, transmission tunnels and fuel cells. 

They are easy to install and form over any surface shape and are are temperate resistant up to 260℃

Zoo Performance Exhaust Heat Wrap is a vital product for heat management and has great benefits such as lowering engine temps and in turn inreasing the life of important engine components. 

It can be used across multiple applications such as air intake, intercoolers, superchargers, turbo pipes and exhaust headers.  It can be secured with stainless steel ties, wire or hose clamps. 

Our wraps are made from extremely durable, tight woven titanium fibres to handle extreme heat of up to 1350°C.  It's highly robust and resistanct to chemicals and oils.

column3:
ZOO PERFORMANCE Turbo Beanies or Turbo Blankets, are constructed using a high temperature pure carbon fibre & titanium material combined with a silica insulation matting under a tight weaved outer layer and a stainless steel reinforced cage. This premium technology is heat rated to 1270 °C both internally and externally. Our new double wall design is created to reduce as much heat as possible from your engine bay and surrounding components.

Turbo beanies are used to separate the turbine housing from the core.  This allows the core to work with less heat strain,  resulting in less of a chance of failing.  The heat energy stays stored within the gas, hotter gases accelerate far better than cooler gases, so reducing the overall effect that it would have on the turbo's lifespan. 

Each Turbo Beanie comes with stainless steel anchoring hooks incorporated into the sheild, as well as spring clips for securing.  

AVAILABLE SIZES: 
T28, T3, T4, T6

COLOURS: 
Carbon Fibre, Titanium

INTERCOOLER / BOOST CLAMPS

Our intercooler/boost clamps are CNC machined from 6061 aircraft grade billet aluminum and hard anodised with anti-corrosion properties. Supplied with viton O-rings for the optimum seal and easy to install and adjust in those hard to reach places. 


We manufacture these for high pressure and high heat applications with a max operating pressure of 500PSI and a max heat rating of 200 °C there is never a need to worry.   

These specially designed clamps will handle anything you can throw at it and will withstand engine flexing, boost movement, vibrations, lateral misalignments within 12 degrees of axial movement. 

Each kit includes:-
1 x Clamp
